BILL_ACCT
The interval data will consist of 48 intervals (30 mins.) stated in Kilowatts for each day.
Interval one [KW_INTERVAL_1] is from 12:00 am to 12:30 am - Interval 48 [KW_INTERVAL_48] is from 11:30 pm to 12:00 am of day listed.
Historical meter information may appear different than current meter information due to meter exchanges and removals.
This interval data is provided to assist in the development of a customer's load profile curve.
The data for some usage periods for some customers may not have been collected and may need to be estimated.
This data - in its unedited form - should not be used for billing verification purposes.
ComEd provides net results for Prime meter(s).  Meter usage data accumulated from the tenant's subtractive meters or customer's submeters will be subtracted from the prime meter(s).
15,000 kWh evaluation is based on sum of kWh usage for prior calendar year and is applicable to commercial customers only.

Evaluation takes place annually on the second Saturday of March.  If usage request is made between Jan 1 and the 2nd Saturday of March, then the indicator will be based on the calendar year 2 years prior.
E.g. if a usage request is made on Feb 15th, 2013, the indicator will be based on 2011 calendar year usage.
If a usage request is made on April 5th, then it will be s based on 2012 calendar year usage.
